OL,3,CPeople with dementia 'treated like
OL,4,Csecond-class citizens'
OL,6,FPeople with dementia are treated like
OL,7,F'second class citizens' according to a
OL,8,FBristol campaigner who cared for his
OL,9,Fwife for 20 years.
OL,11,FTony Hall, who heads up wants to make
OL,12,FBristol a dementia friendly city.
OL,14,F"People with dementia are treated like
OL,15,Fsecond class citizens, they're
OL,16,Fembarrassed if they've got dementia,
OL,17,Fthey're stigmatised, they're lonely
OL,18,Fand it's got to stop", He told ITV
OL,19,FNews West Country.
